{"id":86,"parent_id":74,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":86,"title":"John 12: Jesus' Final Public Testimony","subtitle":"","short_title":"John 12: Jesus' Final Public Testimony","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony"},[".heading",{"id":"head13","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony.head13"},["h1","John 12"],[".subtitle","Jesus’ Final Public Testimony"],[".intro","If you had lived at the time of Jesus and had seen the things you read about in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/1"},"John 1–11"],", how strong do you think your testimony would have been? Nearly every chapter in John includes not only powerful reasons to have an increased testimony of Jesus but usually also includes an account of those who refused to accept that testimony.",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12"},"John 12"],"is no exception. As you read, notice what it says about those who believe in Jesus and what they do and what it says about those who do not believe in Him and what they do."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12"},"John 12"]],["p.para",{"id":"p255","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony.p255"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.1-7"},"John 12:1–7"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/26.6-13"},"Matthew 26:6–13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/14.3-9"},"Mark 14:3–9"]],["p.para",{"id":"p256","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony.p256"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.12-19"},"John 12:12–19"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/21.1-11"},"Matthew 21:1–11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/11.1-11"},"Mark 11:1–11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/19.28-40"},"Luke 19:28–40"]]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f57","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony.f57"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12"},"John 12"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Ointment of spikenard"],"(v. 3)"],["td","Perfumed cream"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Odour"],"(v. 3)"],["td","Smell, scent"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Three hundred pence"],"(v. 5)"],["td","About a year’s wages for a common laborer"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Consulted"],"(v. 10)"],["td","Counseled together"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Hosanna"],"(v. 13)"],["td","A shout of praise that means “Save now”"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Perceive"],"(v. 19)"],["td","Understand"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Prevail"],"(v. 19)"],["td","Accomplish"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Abideth alone"],"(v. 24)"],["td","Stays as it is"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Esaias"],"(vv. 38–39)"],["td","Isaiah"],["td"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.14-19"},"John 12:14–19"],"—What Was the Significance of Jesus Riding into Jerusalem on a Donkey?"],["p.para",{"id":"p266","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony.p266"},"See “Understanding the Scriptures” for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/21.1-11"},"Matthew 21:1–11"],"(p. 29)."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.25-26"},"John 12:25–26"],"—Are We Really Supposed to Hate Our Own Lives?"],["p.para",{"id":"p267","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony.p267"},"The counsel in these verses is much like the counsel Jesus gave on other occasions to “lose” your life for His sake (for example, see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/16.24-26"},"Matthew 16:24–26"],"). In",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.19"},"Mosiah 3:19"],"we learn that “the natural man is an enemy to God.” It should not be hard to understand that we must hate the kind of life that makes us enemies to God in order to obtain the eternal life Jesus promised in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.25-26"},"John 12:25–26"],"."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.31"},"John 12:31"],"—“The Prince of This World”"],["p.para",{"id":"p268","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony.p268"},"This phrase refers to Satan, the devil. He is “the prince of this world” in the sense that he has great power and influence in this fallen world and rules over the many who have given him power over them.",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.31"},"John 12:31"],"tells us that he will be removed from his position of power at the time of judgment, which will first occur at Christ’s Second Coming."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p269","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony.p269"},"Do activities A and B as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12"},"John 12"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Different Attitudes about Jesus"],[".figure",{"id":"f58","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony.f58"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","List the following people and groups of people in your notebook: Mary (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.1-8"},"John 12:1–8"],"), Judas (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.1-8"},"vv. 1–8"],"), people who came with branches (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.12-18"},"vv. 12–18"],"), Greeks (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.20-22"},"vv. 20–22"],"), chief priests and chief rulers (vv. 10–11, 42–43). After each, tell how you think they felt about Jesus, based on what you read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12"},"John 12"],"."]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Describe two or three righteous principles you are now following in your life that show your love for Jesus Christ."]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"I Am"],["p.para",{"id":"p272","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-12-jesus-final-public-testimony.p272"},"As explained in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/8"},"John 8"],", the phrase “I am” had special meaning to the Jewish people (see “Understanding the Scriptures” for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/8.58"},"John 8:58,"],"p. 82). John recorded many of the special occasions when Jesus chose to testify of who He is and of His mission with an “I am” statement. List and read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/6.35,41,48,51"},"John 6:35, 41, 48, 51"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/8.12"},"8:12"],"(and 12:46); 10:7, 9, 11, 14; 11:25; 14:6; and 15:1, 5. After each scripture reference, briefly explain what it teaches us about the mission of Jesus Christ."]]]]]]],"refs":null}
